    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/706.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Nicaragua</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Minister of Nicaragua presents his compliments to his excellency the
                    Secretary of State and begs to inform his excellency that to-day he has received
                    a cable from his Government advising <pb facs="1069" n="953" xml:id="pg_953"/>
                    that finally an agreement has been reached with the New York bankers, Messrs.
                    Brown Brothers &amp; Co. and J. &amp; W. Seligman &amp; Co., who will furnish
                    the Government five hundred thousand cordobas in order to pay the salaries past
                    due.</p>
                <p>In view of this new agreement I respectfully request of your excellency to
                    suspend for the time being all negotiations and consider it unnecessary to call
                    upon the bankers or their representatives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Nicaragua</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
